**System Behaviour**

**Form Flow**

**New client online booking:** Client books via Rejuvenate website →
system checks if consultation form exists → if NO, redirects to digital
consultation form before confirming booking → form submitted → system
runs contraindication check against booked treatment → if BLOCK,
appointment auto-cancelled with explanation → if FLAG, appointment
confirmed but therapist receives alert → booking confirmed with SMS +
email.

**Returning client:** System checks form expiry (6-month validity) → if
expired, prompts re-review before next appointment → if medical changes
flagged, re-runs contraindication logic.

**Walk-in client:** Therapist sends consultation form link via SMS to
client's phone → client fills on their device in-clinic → therapist
reviews on their dashboard → proceeds or flags issues.

**Patch Test Tracking**

First-time clients for microneedling and chemical peels require a patch
test. The system should auto-schedule a patch test appointment (15 min,
no charge) 48 hours before the treatment appointment. If patch test not
completed, treatment appointment status changes to 'Pending Patch Test'
and cannot be checked in.

**Aftercare Automation**

On appointment completion, the system auto-sends treatment-specific
aftercare instructions via email (15--30 mins after). Content is
pre-configured per treatment type. Delivery is logged for insurance
documentation. Natalie already has aftercare content on her website ---
we pull this into the system as templates.

**Treatment Record Per Session**

**Microneedling:** Needle cartridge type, depth per area, serum applied,
skin response notes, before/after photos

**Chemical peel:** Peel type/brand, concentration, application time,
layers, neutralisation time, skin response

**RF Needling:** Device/handpiece, temperature settings, passes per
area, energy level, skin response

**Polynucleotides:** Product/brand, volume injected, injection sites
(mark on face diagram), batch number

